# Sentinel Browse Extension — Production Upgrade

This plan upgrades the extension accuracy, reduces false positives, and makes it behave like a real-world cybersecurity product while preserving all existing working code.

## Proposed Changes

---

### New Utility Module

#### [NEW] [domainWhitelist.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/detection/domainWhitelist.js)

A centralized whitelist and search-engine-aware helper (exported functions used by [signature.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/detection/signature.js) and [advancedEngine.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/detection/advancedEngine.js)):
- `TRUSTED_DOMAINS` — expanded list (google, bing, youtube, microsoft, github, apple, amazon, wikipedia, linkedin, twitter/x, cloudflare, mozilla, openai)
- `SEARCH_ENGINE_HOSTS` — { google.com, bing.com, duckduckgo.com, yahoo.com, baidu.com }
- `getRootDomain(url)` — extracts **root eTLD+1** only (strips subdomains) using URL API
- [isTrustedDomain(url)](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/detection/advancedEngine.js#46-49) — checks root domain via `endsWith()`
- `isSearchEngineQuery(url)` — returns `true` only when host is a search engine **and** path starts with `/search` or query contains `q=`

---

### Detection Engine Fixes

#### [MODIFY] [signature.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/detection/signature.js)

**Problem:** flags `google.com/search?q=login+verify` as malicious because `login`/`verify` keywords appear in the URL.

**Fix:**
- Import [isTrustedDomain](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/detection/advancedEngine.js#46-49), `isSearchEngineQuery` from `domainWhitelist.js`
- Before keyword scan, return `{ flag: false }` if URL is a trusted domain or a search engine query
- This prevents ALL false positives on whitelisted/search URLs

#### [MODIFY] [advancedEngine.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/detection/advancedEngine.js)

Key improvements across all 8 task steps:

**Step 1 – False positives:** Use `getRootDomain()` for domain extraction; gate keyword penalty behind `!isTrustedDomain` AND `!isSearchEngineQuery`

**Step 2 – Trust Engine (weighted scoring):**
| Factor | Weight change |
|---|---|
| Safe Browsing match | +5 (was +4) |
| Dataset match | +4 (was +3) |
| ML malicious | +3 (was +2) |
| Signature match | +3 (unchanged) |
| Obfuscation | +2 (unchanged) |
| Behavior flag | +2 (unchanged) |
| IP address used | +2 (unchanged) |
| Long URL (>150) | +1 (unchanged) |
| High dot count (>5) | +1 (unchanged) |
| Special chars (>=6) | +1 (unchanged) |
| **Trusted domain** | **–5 (was –3)** |
| Reputable profile | –3 (was –2) |

**Step 4 – Context-aware detection:** `isSearchEngineQuery()` check gates keyword score; body of conditionals adds explicit reason `"Search engine query on trusted domain"`

**Step 7 – Decision engine priority (strictly enforced):**
```
1. safeBrowsing.isMalicious → MALICIOUS (hard override)
2. dataset.flag → MALICIOUS (hard override)
3. score > 5 AND totalSignals >= 2 → MALICIOUS
4. score > 2 OR suspiciousSignalCount >= 1 → SUSPICIOUS
5. else → SAFE
```

**Step 8 – Structured logging:** [analyzeUrlAdvanced](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/detection/advancedEngine.js#68-268) returns `logPayload` field with `{ url, domain, score, trustScore, status, reasons }` consumed by [background.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/background.js)

---

### Background Orchestration

#### [MODIFY] [background.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/background.js)

**Step 8 – Enhanced [logFinalResult()](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/background.js#149-159):**  
Log full structured object: `url`, `domain`, `score`, `trustScore`, `status`, `reasons[]`, `sources[]`, `signalCount`

Minor: already delegates correctly to `handleMaliciousUrl / handleSuspiciousUrl / handleSafeUrl` — no structural changes needed.

---

### Adaptive Learning

#### [MODIFY] [adaptiveProfile.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/utils/adaptiveProfile.js)

**Step 5 – Enhance [getDomainProfileSnapshot()](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/utils/adaptiveProfile.js#21-50):**
- If `safeVisits >= 5` AND `maliciousDetections === 0` → `trustBoost = true` (used in advancedEngine to give –2 bonus)
- If `maliciousDetections >= 3` OR `riskRatio >= 0.6` → `highRisk = true` (used for +2 bonus)
- These two new boolean fields feed into the scoring in [advancedEngine.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/detection/advancedEngine.js)

---

### UI/UX Improvements

#### [MODIFY] [content.js](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/content.js)

**Step 6 – Enhanced overlay:**
- **Safe:** green gradient, trust score badge (top-right), auto-hide 3s, shield icon ✅
- **Suspicious:** amber gradient, ⚠️ icon, show reasons list, sound plays, auto-hide 6s  
- **Malicious:** deep red gradient, 🚫 icon, show reasons, NO auto-hide, pointer-events enabled (user can dismiss)
- Add dismiss `×` button on suspicious/malicious overlays
- Overlay now 300px wide, uses smoother slide-in animation

---

### Warning Page

#### [MODIFY] [warning.html](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/warning.html)

**Step 6 – Malicious block page:**
- Add animated pulsing red border on card
- Add `Trust Score` mini-card to transparency grid (was missing)
- Display "MALICIOUS SITE BLOCKED" badge more prominently with larger font
- Show `domain` extracted from URL as a highlighted field

