## Verification Plan

### Manual Testing in Chrome (Load Unpacked)

1. Open `chrome://extensions`, enable Developer Mode, click **Load unpacked**, select `d:\sentinel-browse-extension`
2. Navigate to `https://www.google.com/search?q=login+verify` → **Expected**: ✅ Green overlay "Safe Website" (no false positive)
3. Navigate to `https://paypal-login-secure.com` → **Expected**: 🚫 Redirect to warning.html (dataset match → MALICIOUS)
4. Navigate to `https://192.168.1.1` → **Expected**: ⚠️ Yellow overlay "Suspicious" with reason "Uses IP address instead of domain"
5. Navigate to `https://github.com` → **Expected**: ✅ Green overlay with 95+ trust score
6. Open [dashboard.html](file:///d:/sentinel-browse-extension/dashboard.html) via extension popup → Run Simulation with `http://fake-google-login.xyz/verify` → **Expected**: MALICIOUS verdict with reasons
7. Check DevTools console (background service worker) → Verify log output contains `[Sentinel] Final Decision:` with full structured object including `domain`, `score`, `trustScore`, `reasons[]`

### Console Log Verification

In the Chrome DevTools background service worker console, each scan should log:
```json
{
  "url": "...",
  "domain": "...",
  "score": 7,
  "trustScore": 25,
  "status": "malicious",
  "reasons": ["..."],
  "signalCount": 3
}
```

> [!NOTE]
> There are no automated tests in this project. All verification is via Chrome's extension loading flow and manual browser navigation.
